Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Gisèle","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["name of Frankish origin, from the Germanic word <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. It was a common practice in medieval Europe to leave children as pledges for an alliance, to be brought up at a foreign court, and the name may be derived as a byname from this practice. This was the name by which the wife of  Duke Rollo  of Normandy (  <i>c.</i>860– <i>c.</i>930 ) was known. On her account the name enjoyed considerable popularity in France from an early period. Use of the name in English-speaking countries is much more recent, and is due mainly to the ballet Giselle (first performed in  1841 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Gisella","meanings":["name of Frankish origin, from the Germanic word <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. It was a common practice in medieval Europe to leave children as pledges for an alliance, to be brought up at a foreign court, and the name may be derived as a byname from this practice. This was the name by which the wife of  Duke Rollo  of Normandy (  <i>c.</i>860– <i>c.</i>930 ) was known. On her account the name enjoyed considerable popularity in France from an early period. Use of the name in English-speaking countries is much more recent, and is due mainly to the ballet Giselle (first performed in  1841 )."]},{"name":"Gisele","meanings":["name of Frankish origin, from the Germanic word <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. It was a common practice in medieval Europe to leave children as pledges for an alliance, to be brought up at a foreign court, and the name may be derived as a byname from this practice. This was the name by which the wife of  Duke Rollo  of Normandy (  <i>c.</i>860– <i>c.</i>930 ) was known. On her account the name enjoyed considerable popularity in France from an early period. Use of the name in English-speaking countries is much more recent, and is due mainly to the ballet Giselle (first performed in  1841 )."]},{"name":"Gisela","meanings":["from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ or ‘scion’.  See  <b>Giselle</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gisèle de Rollancourt was born in 1168, in Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France, her father, Hugues d'Ardres, was 32 and her mother, Jeanne de Rollancourt, was 29. She had at least 2 daughters with Evrard DE BERGHES SAINT WINOC-DE SELVESSE. She died in 1214, in Bergues, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1168–1214":"1168–1214","1156–1219":"1156–1219","1180–1248":"1180–1248","1158–1211":"1158–1211","1187–Female":"1187–Surnud","1189–1244":"1189–1244","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1139–1200":"1139–1200","1187":"1187","1180":"1180","1139":"1139","1248":"1248","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1136":"1136","1168":"1168","1179":"1179","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1156":"1156","1219":"1219","Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Bergues, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Bergues, Nord, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Calais, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1168–1214":"1168–1214","1156–1219":"1156–1219","1180–1248":"1180–1248","1158–1211":"1158–1211","1187–Female":"1187–Kuollut","1189–1244":"1189–1244","1136–1179":"1136–1179","1139–1200":"1139–1200","1187":"1187","1180":"1180","1139":"1139","1248":"1248","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1136":"1136","1168":"1168","1179":"1179","1189":"1189","1200":"1200","1211":"1211","1244":"1244","1156":"1156","1219":"1219","Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Rollancourt, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Rollancourt, Pas